    {
      "title": "Present tense of -are verbs",
      "level": "A1",
      "function": "Talk about what people do",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 7,
      "explanation": "The biggest family. Drop -are, add: -o, -i, -a, -iamo, -ate, -ano (parlare → parlo, parli, parla, parliamo, parlate, parlano). Because the ending names the person, the pronoun usually stays home.",
